[2] Brazil: influenza H1N1 & H3N2
- Serra (Espírito Santo): H3N2
Date: Tue 15 May 2018
Source: Portal Temponovo [in Portuguese, machine trans., edited]
https://portaltemponovo.com.br/serra-registra-primeira-morte-por-influenza-h3n2-em-2018/


The communications department of Serra [municipality, Espírito Santo state] confirmed the 1st death of "super-flu" in the municipality in 2018. The case is a resident who was diagnosed with influenza A/H3N2. In addition, there is another confirmed case of H3N2 and 49 suspected cases of severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS; SRAG in Portuguese) in the city.

According to the city, approximately 54 900 people have been vaccinated against influenza. The vaccination campaign continues until 1 Jun 2018, in all units of Serra. In the regional units (Jacaraípe, Novo Horizonte, Feu Rosa, Serra-sede [center], Serra Dourada, and Boa Vista), from 7:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. In the other units, according to the schedule of the vaccination center of each unit.

The communication office of the municipality was asked whether the vaccination would be available to all residents, to which it replied that the priority group receiving the influenza vaccine is defined by the Ministry of Health, and that so far the city has not received guidelines for vaccination of persons who are not in the priority group.

Another case that was under investigation is a 34-year-old woman resident of Nova Carapina, who died on 25 Apr 2018. The results released on 3 May 2018 dismissed the death from influenza. The report showed that the woman died of respiratory syndrome and pneumonia. The woman was admitted to the emergency department of Serra-Sede on 22 Apr 2018, with pneumonia. As influenza was suspected, she remained in isolation.

Another death also under investigation was that of a male resident of Vista da Serra. The results released on 10 May 2018 discarded the diagnosis of influenza H1N1 and again confirmed pneumonia as the cause of death.

--
